OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780405872
OL,3,CDoug Beattie resigns from UUP as
OL,4,Cmembership 'no longer tenable'
OL,6,FFormer UUP leader Doug Beattie has
OL,7,Fresigned from the party, citing a
OL,8,F"toxic atmosphere" under its current
OL,9,Fleadership.
OL,11,FMr Beattie, who intends to stay on as
OL,12,Fan independent unionist MLA for Upper
OL,13,FBann, said "an insidious campaign of
OL,14,Frumour and gossip was being waged"
OL,15,Fagainst him, in a letter addressed to
OL,16,Fcurrent party leader, Jon Burrows.
OL,18,FA party spokesperson said they do "not
OL,19,Faccept the characterisation of recent
OL,20,Fevents set out in Mr Beattie's letter".
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@RO]uD@LOUvD@bO]zD@cOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/9
